River delta folk of the Kowloon region, the Deltari built the hydraulic infrastructure
— channels, cisterns, flood defenses, water-quality monitoring — that makes the delta
city viable. Direct heirs of the Reed Ledger Wardens, their civilization is organized
around water-reading and practical record-keeping: the accumulated flow records of a
Deltari settlement can span centuries of continuous hydraulic observation. The Black
Ledger, Kowloon's sealed census of individuals transferred to the Spirebound Conclave,
lists Deltari among the transferred; their oral tradition has preserved those names
across generations while the official records remain sealed and the Jade Magistracy
declines to discuss the matter.
